extends _base

include _index

block head
	title Pricing | Gripeless — Encourage complaining
	+landing-head
	+display-font

mixin feature-row(label)
	.py-3.border-t.border-b.w-full.flex.-mb-px.items-center
		.inline-block.font-medium.text-gray-700.text-center.whitespace-wrap(class="w-1/2")
			= label
		.inline-block.font-bold.text-center(class="w-1/2")
			block

mixin yes
	.text-red-600 ✓

mixin no
	.text-gray-500 ✗

block body
	.font-display
		.mb-16
			+nav

		h1.text-3xl.font-bold.text-center.mb-8 Pricing
		.mx-4: .flex.justify-center.flex-wrap
			.max-w-sm.w-full.bg-gray-100.shadow-2xl.rounded-lg.p-4.border.mb-16.mx-2
				h2.font-bold.text-center.text-xl.mb-2 Free
				p.text-center.text-gray-700.mb-4.max-w-xs.mx-auto
					| Everything you need to get started
				.mx-auto.mb-4.px-4
					+feature-row('Dashboard'): +yes
					+feature-row('Javascript SDK'): +yes
					+feature-row('Screenshots') Unlimited
					+feature-row('Notifications') Mail only

				.text-center.flex.items-center.justify-center.mb-2
					span.text-2xl.font-semibold Free

				p.text-gray-700.text-sm.text-center.mb-4
					span.max-w-xs.inline-block The features in this plan will forever be free. Free plan includes everything that you need to judge whether Gripeless is a right fit for you.

				.text-center
					+create-project-btn

			.max-w-sm.w-full.bg-white.shadow-2xl.rounded-lg.p-4.mb-16.mx-2.border-red-600.border-2
				.-mx-4.-mt-4.text-center.font-black.text-sm.bg-red-600.px-2.py-1.text-gray-100.rounded-t-md.border-red-700.mb-4 Most popular
				h2.font-bold.text-center.text-xl.mb-2 Lite
				p.text-center.text-gray-700.mb-4
					| When things get too serious for free plan
				p.text-sm.mb-2.text-center.font-bold Everything in Free, plus:
				.mx-auto.mb-4.px-4
					+feature-row('Notifications'): +yes
					+feature-row('Support') Priority

				.text-center.flex.items-center.justify-center
					span.text-2xl $
					span.font-bold.text-3xl.tracking-tighter 9
					span.tracking-tight.font-base.text-2xl /month

				p.text-gray-700.text-sm.text-center.mb-4
					a.text-red-800(href="mailto:support@usegripeless.com?subject=%5BBilling%5D%20Longer%20billing%20periods")
						| Contact us
					|  for longer billing periods.

				.text-center
					+create-project-btn

			.max-w-sm.w-full.bg-gray-100.shadow-2xl.rounded-lg.p-4.border.mb-16.mx-2
				h2.font-bold.text-center.text-xl.mb-2 Growth
				p.text-center.text-gray-700.mb-4.mx-8
					| Make Gripeless an integral part of your development
				p.text-sm.mb-2.text-center.font-bold Everything in Lite, plus:
				.mx-auto.mb-4.px-4
					+feature-row('Deep integrations'): +yes
					+feature-row('Remove branding'): +yes

				.text-center.flex.items-center.justify-center
					span.text-2xl $
					span.font-bold.text-3xl.tracking-tighter 39
					span.tracking-tight.font-base.text-2xl /month

				p.text-gray-700.text-sm.text-center.mb-4
					a.text-red-800(href="mailto:support@usegripeless.com?subject=%5BBilling%5D%20Longer%20billing%20periods")
						| Contact us
					|  for longer billing periods.

				.text-center
					+create-project-btn

		.mx-4: .bg-gray-100.mx-auto.max-w-xl.p-4.shadow-xl.border.rounded-lg.mb-16
			p.font-bold.mb-2.text-xl Have an open-source project?
			p As a way to give back to the open-source community we're providing a full, unlimited version of Gripeless for free to open-source projects.
			p
				| If you have an open-source and non-commercial project, please 
				a.text-red-800(href="mailto:support@usegripeless.com?subject=Open%20source%20project") contact us!
		mixin faq(title)
			.mb-4
				h2.text-2xl.font-semibold.mb-2= title
				block

		.mx-4.mb-32: .max-w-3xl.mx-auto
			h1.text-3xl.font-bold.text-center.mb-2 FAQ
			p.text-center.mb-6 Missed your question? #[a.text-red-700(class="hover:text-red-900" href="mailto:support@usegripeless.com") Ask us directly].
			+faq('How can Gripeless make my product more reliable?')
				p.
					Gripeless aims to quickly find any issue that arise when
					you release new version of your product, update
					dependencies, or add a possibly unreliable third party
					provider. Users can quickly report those issues to you
					where so you don't have to wait till someone finally sends
					you an email telling you that stuff is broken.

			+faq('What kind of gripes can I expect to get?')
				p.
					Broken links, broken buttons, unusuable UX issues like
					content overflows on certain devices, problems with flows,
					integrations not being reliable, gripes with anything about
					UX (say user feels like something could work nicer for
					them), pretty much anything that they see and think: "that
					looks pretty broken".

			+faq('Why wouldn\'t I just code this up myself?')
				p.
					Time is valuable. We make sure that the issues always get
					submitted, screenshots are accurate, and your users get
					updated. We upkeep the deep integrations/notifications so
					you can sleep peacefully without worrying that your issue
					reporting software has an issue. That would be pretty bad.

			+faq('Why not simply use a solution like Sentry or Rollbar?')
				p.
					Error tracking software is great, we've personally used
					Sentry in a couple projects and the experience has been
					really nice. Gripeless is aimed at users to report issues
					that traditional error trackers won't catch - things like
					incorrect outputs, slow loading speeds or janky UX that
					won't throw errors anywhere in your code, but only a real
					user will notice that something's wrong.

			+faq('Why not just use my support lines?')
				p.
					Imagine that you spot a nasty bug with your favourite app.
					Would you go through the effort to open your slow email
					client, spend time writing out a nice message, let alone
					attaching a screenshot? You'll also need to attach info
					about your browser, state of the app, etc. Despite seeing
					many issues with products I like I've never done that,
					which is why we've created the gripe reporting widget which
					makes this process 10x easier for us and our users.

			+faq('Why should we trust you?')
				p.
					We really like using reliable products, the more reliable
					products are out there the happier we are. It feels really
					satisfying to see our customers fix the gripes of their
					users for some reason.

			+faq('What is the difference between "Notifications" and "Deep integrations"?')
				p.
					Notifications means that you will receive, well,
					notifications in e.g. Slack, text messages, webhooks, etc. with a link to the gripe on your Gripeless dashboard.
					Deep integrations allow you to take this a step further and
					have gripes be sent into your existing issue tracker, like
					GitHub issues, Jira, Asana, etc.

			+faq('I already use x, I don\'t want to bombard my users with more widgets!')
				p Gripeless' activation button doesn't stay fixed on your site (unless you make it to yourself). Instead, it integrates seamlessly into the look of your website - #[a.text-red-700(class="hover:text-red-900" href='/docs#Goal') we've created a few examples] to show how Gripeless can be installed without making your site look crowded.

			+faq('Can you make me a custom x or customize the widget for me?')
				p.
					Likely! Message our support and we'll try to work something
					out.

			+faq('Why can I not see the screenshot button sometimes?')
				p.
					The screenshots feature is supported only on Blink and
					Gecko based browsers (e.g. Chrome, Opera, Firefox, combines
					to ~85% market share). Also, the screenshots currently
					don't work on mobile due to the screenshots UI only being
					optimized for mouse use, but this might change in the
					future.

		.mb-32
			+features

		+foot


	+landing-script
